        <h1> Private tour guide in Ravenna, Bologna, Ferrara - Italy
</h1>
        <p> Ciao, Hi, Bonjour, Hola.... and welcome to Emilia-Romagna, Italy! I am a licensed guide in Emilia Romagna. I was born in the Ravenna Province and I lived here for more than 30 years. I also lived many years abroad, but I always felt a deep love for my Region and never lost the chance to pass it on to the friends I've met when I was living abroad. I am now back in Italy and since 2013, when I got my licence, I've been trying to share this love with all the people who would like to enjoy the immense artistic and cultural heritage that Emilia Romagna can offer... <br><br>Ravenna with its unique mosaics (8 UNESCO sites). Ferrara, UNESCO Renascence jewel, and its "Delta del Po" National Park. Bologna, with its medieval towers, enchanting squares and churches. The beautiful landscape with its dreamy hills, medieval villages and warm sea. <br>And of course the delights of local food and wine and the colourful traditions and festivals. <br><br>Just call me or write!  I will be pleased to guide you through my standard tours as well Tour guide services/sample itinerary:as through a personalized visit. And if I'm not available when you need me.....DON'T WORRY, I can arrange your tour with another licensed guide.</p><br>
        <p>You can view more of Emilia Romagna <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emilia-Romagna" target="_blank">here</a>.</p><br>
        <h1>Tour guide services/sample itinerary:</h1>
        3 HOUR TOURS</p><br><p>RAVENNA</p><p>3 hours will give you the chance to discover some of the best examples of the unique Early-Christian and Byzantine mosaics such as:</p><p><li> Church of S.Vitale. In its mosaics the Emperor Justinian is masterfully depicted with his fabulous wife Theodora.</li></p><p><li> Mausoleum of Galla Placidia, a powerful building created to honour the Empress of the Western Roman Empire.</li></p><p><li> Neoniano Baptistery equally decorated by wonderful mosaics.</li></p><p><li> Basilica of Sant'Apollinare Nuovo which was the private chapel of the Ostrogoths King Theoderic. </li></p><p>All these marvels can be seen by taking an easy stroll through the centre of Ravenna. During our walk in the pedestrian area you'll have the chance to step into a mosaic workshop, have a pause for coffee in the main square and visit the Tomb of the poet Dante Alighieri (Divine Comedy) who died here in 1321.</p><p>Although for a complete visit to Ravenna I suggest a full-day guided tour (6 hour tour + lunch break) which includes other UNESCO monuments.<br> In the centre: the Archiepiscopal Museum housing the renowned 6th century ivory throne and the Chapel of Saint Andrew, the King Theodoric's Arian Baptistery (early 6th century) and the marvellous Byzantine mosaics of Sant'Apollinare in Classe located 4 km away from town.</p><br>
        <h2>Transportation by tour guide</h2>
        <p>Yes, transportation can be arranged upon request.  I am not a driver but I can arrange for a private taxi.</p>
